  "issue_title": "\"I/O operation on closed file\" error with CliRunner and echo_via_pager under 8.4",
  "issue_body": "When `echo_via_pager` is used in the command, `CliRunner.invoke` fails with:\n\n> ValueError: I/O operation on closed file.\n\nThis started happening with Click 8.4, does not happen with 8.3.3.\n\nReproducer:\n```python\nfrom click import command, echo_via_pager\nfrom click.testing import CliRunner\n\n@command()\ndef cli():\n    echo_via_pager(\"Hello, Click!\")\n\nrunner = CliRunner()\nrunner.invoke(cli)\n```\n\nTraceback:\n```\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \".../echo_via_pager.py\", line 11, in <module>\n    runner.invoke(cli)\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^\n  File \".../.venv/echo-via-pager/lib/python3.13/site-packages/click/testing.py\", line 676, in invoke\n    sys.stdout.flush()\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^\nValueError: I/O operation on closed file.\n```\n\nEnvironment:\n\n- OS: Ubuntu 24.04.4, Linux 6.17\n- Python version: 3.13.5\n- Click version: 8.4\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-22T03:40:19Z",
